This iterative matrix algorithm is the hot loop of my application. I think restructuring the loop to reduce redundant computation should speed it up. Can you optimize it?

```matlab
function W = iterativeSolver(data, nIter)
    % data: 128 x 50000 matrix (128 channels, 50000 samples)
    % W: 128 x 128 weight matrix
    [nCh, nSamples] = size(data);
    W = eye(nCh);
    lrate = 0.001;

    for iter = 1:nIter
        % Compute activations
        u = W * data;

        % Nonlinearity: logistic sigmoid gradient
        y = 1 ./ (1 + exp(-u));

        % Weight update: natural gradient
        dW = (eye(nCh) + (1 - 2*y) * u') * W;
        W = W + lrate * dW / nSamples;
    end
end
```

