This function classifies sensor readings into quality categories. It's called millions of times in my data pipeline and is slow. Can you optimize it?

```matlab
function categories = classifySensorData(readings, thresholds)
    % readings: 1e6 x 1 vector of sensor values
    % thresholds: [10, 25, 50, 75, 100] — bin edges for quality categories
    % Returns: categories — integer category (1-5) for each reading

    n = numel(readings);
    categories = zeros(n, 1);

    for i = 1:n
        if readings(i) <= thresholds(1)
            categories(i) = 1;
        elseif readings(i) <= thresholds(2)
            categories(i) = 2;
        elseif readings(i) <= thresholds(3)
            categories(i) = 3;
        elseif readings(i) <= thresholds(4)
            categories(i) = 4;
        else
            categories(i) = 5;
        end
    end
end
```

